This program tests the compiler's ability to recover from some syntactical errors
to do with variable declarations
These errors include:
int y = 4; - Cannot assign a variable a value and declare it at the same time
int a, b; - Cannot declare multiple variables on the same line
int c[] - Missing a number inside the square brackets for the size of the array
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------- */


void main(void)
{
  int y = 4;
  int x;
  int a, b;
  int c[];

  if (x < 4 )
  {
    x = x + 1;
  }
  print(x);

  return;
}
